Reasoning: The paper focuses on a large-scale visual learning setup with a long-tail distribution and semantic relations between facts, which are all relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of visual semantic embeddings and adaptation of existing datasets also suggest a natural language processing (cs.CL) component. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of lifelong learning (LLL) and the need for efficient and effective LLL methods, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
